# Implementation Plan: MCP + A2A/CAP on CoAgent4U

> **Goal:** Evolve the existing CoAgent4U codebase into a privacy-centric personal agent platform with MCP for resource management and CoAgent Protocol (CAP) for agent-to-agent collaboration.

> **Scope:** Personal agent + collaborative tasks only. No Agent Store.

> **Codebase:** Java 21, Spring Boot 3.4, Maven multi-module, hexagonal architecture.

---

## Phase 1: MCP Integration (Weeks 1–2)

> **Goal:** Agent accesses user resources (calendar, drive, email) via the MCP protocol instead of direct adapter calls. This makes the agent extensible — any new resource = a new MCP server, no agent code changes.

### Why MCP First?

MCP is the foundation. Once the agent talks MCP, adding Google Drive, Gmail, or any future resource is just spinning up another MCP server. The agent runtime doesn't change.

```
BEFORE (current):
  AgentCommandService → CalendarPort → GoogleCalendarAdapter → Google API

AFTER (with MCP):
  AgentRuntime → MCP Client → [Calendar MCP Server] → GoogleCalendarAdapter → Google API
                             → [Drive MCP Server]    → GoogleDriveAdapter   → Drive API
                             → [Email MCP Server]    → GmailAdapter         → Gmail API
```

