#### [NEW] `ConsentEngine.java`

```java
package com.coagent4u.a2a.consent;

/**
 * Evaluates an IntentDeclaration against the user's permission rules.
 * 
 * Decision flow:
 * 1. Is the requester BLOCKED? → DENY
 * 2. Does the intent match an auto-approve rule? → AUTO_APPROVE
 * 3. Otherwise → PROMPT_USER (sends Slack approval request via existing ApprovalPort)
 */
public class ConsentEngine {

    private final ContactPersistencePort contactPort;
    private final PrivacyRulePersistencePort rulesPort;
    private final ApprovalPort approvalPort;        // REUSE existing approval module!

    public ConsentResponse evaluate(IntentDeclaration intent, UserId targetUserId) {
        // 1. Check blocked list
        Contact contact = contactPort.findByOwnerAndContact(targetUserId, intent.fromAgent());
        if (contact != null && contact.getTrustLevel() == TrustLevel.BLOCKED) {
            return ConsentResponse.denied("Blocked");
        }

        // 2. Check auto-approve rules
        if (contact != null && contact.isAutoApproveFor(intent.intent())) {
            SharingLevel level = contact.getDefaultSharingLevel();
            return ConsentResponse.autoApproved(level);
        }

        // 3. Prompt user via Slack (reuses existing approval workflow!)
        ApprovalId approvalId = approvalPort.requestConsentApproval(
            targetUserId, intent.fromAgent(), intent.purpose(), intent.dataNeeded());
        return ConsentResponse.pendingApproval(approvalId);
    }
}
```

> [!TIP]
> **The ConsentEngine reuses your existing `approval-module`!** The same Slack interactive buttons that handle meeting approvals now handle data-sharing consent. Zero new UI work.

